---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Campbell K9s Privacy Policy — How We Protect Your Data"
  description="Campbell K9s privacy policy: what information we collect, how we use it, and your rights."
>
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-28 sm:px-10 sm:py-36 lg:px-8 lg:py-44">
    <p class="caption text-brand-accent">Legal</p>
    <h1 class="mt-6 font-serif text-4xl leading-tight sm:text-5xl">
      Privacy Policy
    </h1>
    <p class="caption mt-4 text-brand-primary/50">Effective Date: July 2026</p>

    <div class="mt-12 hairline max-w-[3rem]"></div>

    <div class="mt-12 space-y-10 text-base leading-relaxed text-brand-primary/80 sm:text-lg">
      <p>
        Campbell K9s, LLC (“we”, “us”, or “our") respects your privacy and is
        committed to protecting it through compliance with this Policy. This
        Policy describes the types of information we may collect and our
        practices for using, maintaining, and disclosing that information.
      </p>

      <div>
        <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl text-brand-primary">1. Information We Collect</h2>
        <p class="mt-4">
          We collect several types of information, including:
        </p>
        <ul class="mt-4 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6">
          <li>
            <strong>Personal Information:</strong> Name, address, email address,
            phone number, and any other information you provide when registering
            for an account or requesting service.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Transaction Information:</strong> Details about purchases,
            including payment information and billing details.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Automatic Collection:</strong> IP addresses, browser types,
            and details of your visits to our Services collected through cookies,
            web beacons, and other tracking technologies.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl text-brand-primary">2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
        <p class="mt-4">
          We use information that we collect about you to:
        </p>
        <ul class="mt-4 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6">
          <li>Provide the Services and their content to you.</li>
          <li>Fulfill the purposes for which you provided the information.</li>
          <li>Communicate with you about your account, orders, or subscriptions.</li>
          <li>
            Carry out our obligations and enforce our rights, including billing
            and collection.
          </li>
          <li>Detect and prevent security breaches or fraudulent activity.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl text-brand-primary">3. Sharing Your Information</h2>
        <p class="mt-4">
          We may disclose personal information:
        </p>
        <ul class="mt-4 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6">
          <li>
            To our subsidiaries and affiliates for business purposes.
          </li>
          <li>
            To service providers and contractors who support our business and are
            bound by confidentiality.
          </li>
          <li>To comply with any court order, law, or legal process.</li>
          <li>To enforce our Terms of Service and other agreements.</li>
          <li>With your consent for any other purpose.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl text-brand-primary">4. Your Choices</h2>
        <ul class="mt-4 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6">
          <li>
            <strong>Tracking Technologies:</strong> You can set your browser to
            refuse all or some cookies, though some parts of the Services may
            then be inaccessible.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Promotional Offers:</strong> You can opt out of receiving
            promotional emails by following the instructions in those emails or
            contacting us directly.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Access and Correction:</strong> You may send us an email to
            request access to, correct, or remove personal information you have
            provided.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl text-brand-primary">5. State-Specific Rights</h2>
        <ul class="mt-4 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6">
          <li>
            <strong>California Residents:</strong> You have the right to request
            disclosure of the categories and specific pieces of personal
            information we have collected, the right to request deletion, and the
            right to opt out of the sale or sharing of your information.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Virginia Residents:</strong> You have the right to confirm
            whether we are processing your data, the right to correct
            inaccuracies, and the right to obtain a portable copy of your data.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl text-brand-primary">6. Data Security</h2>
        <p class="mt-4">
          We have implemented measures designed to secure your personal
          information from accidental loss and unauthorized access. All
          information is stored on secure servers. However, the safety of your
          information also depends on you; please keep your account password
          confidential.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl text-brand-primary">7. Contact Information</h2>
        <p class="mt-4">
          To ask questions or comment about this Privacy Policy and our privacy
          practices, contact us at:
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4">
          Campbell K9s, LLC<br />
          278 Old County Road, Smithfield, RI 02917<br />
          <a
            href="mailto:k9campbellmatt@gmail.com"
            class="border-b border-brand-primary/30 pb-0.5 transition-colors hover:border-brand-accent hover:text-brand-accent"
          >
            k9campbellmatt@gmail.com
          </a>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
